19/10/21, 9:21 pm - HSAğŸ¤™ğŸ»: Acknowledge the emotion
The last thing that a grieving person wants is to have their pain downplayed or dismissed. Thatâ€™s why acknowledging their emotions is such an important part of what to say to someone who lost a parent.

Trying to change that personâ€™s emotion is not the way to approach it. While your caring and compassionate heart may want to cheer up the person, itâ€™s best not to tell them to look for a â€œbright sideâ€ or tell them that their loved one is in a better place. Instead, offer condolences that acknowledge the grieving individualâ€™s deep pain and heartache.

30/11/21, 9:27 pm - HSAğŸ¤™ğŸ»: Shared route
From Thiruvathukkal to Cement Junction via Bypass Rd.

45 min (3.7Â km)


1. Head south
2. Turn left toward Pulinakal Boat Jetty Rd
3. Turn right onto Pulinakal Boat Jetty Rd
4. Turn left toward Pathinaril Chira Rd
5. Turn right onto Pathinaril Chira Rd
6. Turn left to stay on Pathinaril Chira Rd
7. Turn right to stay on Pathinaril Chira Rd
8. Turn right
9. Turn left
10. Turn left onto Bypass Rd
11. Turn left onto Cement Rd
12. Arrive at location: Cement Junction
To see this route visit https://maps.app.goo.gl/DFBTwTEfexEv7Lfh9

01/12/21, 8:38 am - HSAğŸ¤™ğŸ»: Fighting for human rights isn't always easy, but who's to say we can't have some fun while we're at it? Our first fundraiser involves a Discord event hosted by our club, Girl Up Sky on December 3, 2021 -- a murder mystery game night that is sure to leave you with the thrill of the chase. We are delighted to invite you to have a fun and entertaining time. 

All proceeds will go to Justice and Hope, an NGO that supports victims of sexual assault, domestic violence and human trafficking. https://instagram.com/justiceandhope1?utm_medium=copy_link

And here is the best part, we are collaborating with amazing small businesses to bring to you amazing gifts if you solve the mystery! Win cookies, beanies, jewellery, coasters and so much more while contributing to our initiative :)

Bring your friends along to enjoy solving a case while supporting a good cause!

Love, 
Team GirlUp Sky

11/04/22, 4:52 pm - HSAğŸ¤™ğŸ»: The NEO Educational Foundation presents to you 
The 6th National Engineering Olympiad!

The National Engineering Olympiad is a competitive platform for the engineering students to showcase your aptitude skills and represent yourself at the national level.

Register now and participate!
https://neoeducation.in/?refid=424011104

The Rounds:
Similar to the previous five editions of the National Engineering Olympiad, the exam will be conducted in two rounds.

Round 1: Basic Aptitude Test- 60 mins, 60 questions. 
Round 1 (Phase 2) Dates are 28th & 29th April 2022. 

Round 2: Technical Ability Test- Online MCQ Exam based on your syllabus of the year & branch you are studying in. 

Please Note:
Both rounds are to be attempted online from your home!

The Rewards: 

For the top performers:
-Top 10 of each year & branch will be awarded a Medal of Excellence.
-Top 30 of each year & branch will be awarded a Certificate of Excellence.

For all participants:
-Guaranteed Internships in various domains.
-A national-level participation certificate.
-Career-oriented webinars by experts for free.

(More details are available on the website)

Don't delay! Registration is now open!
Visit https://neoeducation.in/?refid=424011104

15/04/22, 12:33 pm - HSAğŸ¤™ğŸ»: The NEO Educational Foundation presents to you 
The 6th National Engineering Olympiad!

The National Engineering Olympiad is a competitive platform for the engineering students to showcase your aptitude skills and represent yourself at the national level.

Register now and participate!
https://neoeducation.in/?refid=424011104

The Rounds:
Similar to the previous five editions of the National Engineering Olympiad, the exam will be conducted in two rounds.

Round 1: Basic Aptitude Test- 60 mins, 60 questions. 
Round 1  (Phase 2)  Dates are 28th & 29th April 2022. 

Round 2: Technical Ability Test- Online MCQ Exam based on your syllabus of the year & branch you are studying in. 

Please Note:
Both rounds are to be attempted online from your home!

The Rewards: 

For the top performers:
-Top 10 of each year & branch will be awarded a Medal of Excellence.
-Top 30 of each year & branch will be awarded a Certificate of Excellence.

For all participants:
-Guaranteed Internships in various domains.
-A national-level participation certificate.
-Career-oriented webinars by experts for free.

(More details are available on the website)

Don't delay! Registration is now open!
